is this normal my rabbit just sit in the back of his cage and will bite if anyone holds him but when i pet him he begs to be held he even follows me around the house i hope this helps people are often shocked the first time they see a rabbit display anger bunnies after all are supposed to be timid and sweet not outspoken and nasty and the sudden appearance of sharp teeth and raking claws can be disarming but whether your rabbit is nipping the hand that feeds him chasing you across the room or latching his teeth into your calf it's not unusual and it's not hopeless in fact working with an aggressive rabbit can be extremely rewarding many house rabbit society members have found that aggressive rabbits are often very intelligent animals who are just trying to express themselves once they're given some respect and some ground rules that expression can turn to boundless energy enthusiasm and affection Domestic rabbit Cat Rabbit Ferret Dog Fancy rat Unreal Bugs Bunny European Rabbit Poker jargon Looney Tunes and Merrie Melodies filmography Hamster Guinea pig Dog training The Legend of Zelda series enemies Milton H. Erickson Bat Livestock Tyrannosaurus rex Who Framed Roger Rabbit Bat Boy German Shepherd Dog One Piece minor characters KaBlam! Trapping Mickey Mouse Breastfeeding Rabbits in Australia Minor characters in Sonic the Hedgehog Pet skunk Venom (comics) Animal communication Race X Taboo food and drink Perfect Dark Professional wrestling match types Johnny the Homicidal Maniac Codename: Kids Next Door Prince Edmund (Blackadder) Normal distribution Brown Bear Doom enemies Minor Harry Potter Beasts BZFlag Housebreaking Minor characters in Teen Titans (animated series) Pysanka Goatse.cx 2000 Australian Grand Prix Yu-Gi-Oh! anime and manga characters Sperm Whale Bangladeshi cricket team in Sri Lanka in 2005-06 Red Dwarf characters The Care Bears Adventure in Wonderland Pulp Fiction Falconry Horse Rabbit (zodiac) Scorpion (Mortal Kombat) Tooth enamel Gray Wolf Social rule